00:53:08,753 --> 00:53:12,188
Have I got something on my face?

1060
00:53:12,190 --> 00:53:15,324
No.

1061
00:53:17,528 --> 00:53:19,795
[ BEEP, MACHINERY WHIRS ]

1062
00:53:22,733 --> 00:53:24,233
SKINNER: Cage!

1063
00:53:24,235 --> 00:53:26,602
We've been lookin' everywhere for you.

1064
00:53:26,604 --> 00:53:28,571
Cage!

1065
00:53:28,573 --> 00:53:29,939
Cage, we've been lookin'--

1066
00:53:29,941 --> 00:53:31,307
guys.

1067
00:53:31,309 --> 00:53:34,743
Guys. Can we... just...

1068
00:53:34,745 --> 00:53:35,778
Not do this today?

1069
00:53:35,780 --> 00:53:37,680
What are you talkin' about?

1070
00:53:37,682 --> 00:53:40,416
Farell almost strung us up by our bollocks

1071
00:53:40,418 --> 00:53:41,383
for losing track of you!

1072
00:53:41,385 --> 00:53:43,786
[ GRUNTS ]

1073
00:53:43,788 --> 00:53:45,421
Okay... Skinner. Watch this.

1074
00:53:45,423 --> 00:53:48,991
Now I'm gonna close my eyes.

1075
00:53:48,993 --> 00:53:50,693
Ready? Yeah.

1076
00:53:51,729 --> 00:53:54,763
[ GRUNTS, GROANS ]

1077
00:53:54,765 --> 00:53:56,832
Stinking bastard.

1078
00:53:56,834 --> 00:54:00,502
I-I didn't mind the
extra push-ups.

1079
00:54:00,504 --> 00:54:02,671
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING, THUNDER RUMBLES ]

1080
00:54:04,875 --> 00:54:06,809
[ ALARM BLARING ]

1081
00:54:06,811 --> 00:54:08,677
MAN:<i> Could all combat-ready</i>
<i>squadrons proceed directly</i>

1082
00:54:08,679 --> 00:54:10,846
<i>to the allocated drop ships for primary loading.</i>

1083
00:54:10,848 --> 00:54:12,715
FARELL: It's a new day, people.

1084
00:54:12,717 --> 00:54:14,316
Destiny calls.

1085
00:54:14,318 --> 00:54:16,619
The world expects only one thing from us:

1086
00:54:16,621 --> 00:54:17,886
That we will win.

1087
00:54:33,337 --> 00:54:35,004
WOMAN:<i>
...the current situation on the front line.</i>

1088
00:54:35,006 --> 00:54:37,840
<i>Our troops have suffered heavy casualties.</i>

1089
00:54:37,842 --> 00:54:39,408
MAN: [ BRITISH ACCENT
] It's about time

1090
00:54:39,410 --> 00:54:40,876
we showed those things what we're made of.

1091
00:54:40,878 --> 00:54:43,512
My father flew in the battle of Britain.

1092
00:54:43,514 --> 00:54:46,482
Three years before the yanks came into the war.

1093
00:54:46,484 --> 00:54:48,951
Couldn't be broken. Backbone.

1094
00:54:48,953 --> 00:54:51,787
MAN #2: My uncle George landed
on the beach at Normandy.

1095
00:54:51,789 --> 00:54:53,722
Yeah?

1096
00:54:53,724 --> 00:54:56,358
In their day, this war would have been over by now.

1097
00:54:56,360 --> 00:54:58,327
What do they want with us, anyway?

1098
00:54:58,329 --> 00:54:59,962
It's obvious, isn't it?
Minerals.

1099
00:54:59,964 --> 00:55:01,864
Minerals? Yeah, minerals.
Metals.

1100
00:55:01,866 --> 00:55:03,499
Oxygen, they want. Oxygen?
Think about it.

1101
00:55:03,501 --> 00:55:05,467
What difference does it make?

1102
00:55:05,469 --> 00:55:07,536
They're here. They're winning.

1103
00:55:07,538 --> 00:55:10,906
And whatever it is, they're gonna get it.

1104
00:55:10,908 --> 00:55:13,375
Shouldn't you be over there?

1105
00:55:13,377 --> 00:55:15,344
I've been over there.

1106
00:55:15,346 --> 00:55:18,013
More times than anybody.

1107
00:55:18,015 --> 00:55:20,349
As a matter of fact, I'm...

1108
00:55:20,351 --> 00:55:23,852
Usually long dead by now.

1109
00:55:23,854 --> 00:55:26,455
Coward!

1110
00:55:26,457 --> 00:55:28,657
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]

1111
00:55:28,659 --> 00:55:30,526
What's going on?

1112
00:55:30,528 --> 00:55:32,594
The power's gone.

1113
00:55:34,098 --> 00:55:37,933
[ SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

1114
00:55:37,935 --> 00:55:40,936
[ SIREN WAILING ]

1115
00:55:45,710 --> 00:55:47,376
[ ALARM BLARING ]

1116
00:55:47,378 --> 00:55:50,779
[ WOMAN SCREAMS ]

1117
00:55:50,781 --> 00:55:52,648
[ YELLING IN DISTANCE ]

1118
00:56:07,531 --> 00:56:10,132
[ AUTOMATIC WEAPONS FIRING IN DISTANCE ]

1119
00:56:32,957 --> 00:56:36,592
[ GRUNTING ]

1120
00:56:40,464 --> 00:56:42,631
CARTER: I found the Omega.
I found it.

1121
00:56:42,633 --> 00:56:44,833
It has to be here.
Curnera dam, Germany.

1122
00:56:44,835 --> 00:56:46,068
This has got to be it.

1123
00:56:46,070 --> 00:56:47,136
It fits the description perfectly.

1124
00:56:47,138 --> 00:56:47,970
Yes, you found it.

1125
00:56:47,972 --> 00:56:49,805
Again.

1126
00:56:49,807 --> 00:56:51,573
What difference does it make?

1127
00:56:51,575 --> 00:56:53,809
'Cause we're never gonna get there.

1128
00:56:53,811 --> 00:56:55,978
No matter what we do...

1129
00:56:55,980 --> 00:56:59,681
No matter how carefully we plan,

1130
00:56:59,683 --> 00:57:02,584
we can't get off that beach.

1131
00:57:02,586 --> 00:57:04,720
[ CLANGING ]

1132
00:57:11,429 --> 00:57:12,661
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

1133
00:57:12,663 --> 00:57:15,531
You can do this. You can.

1134
00:57:15,533 --> 00:57:18,901
You keep coming here every day and I'll train you.

1135
00:57:20,938 --> 00:57:23,472
You already have.

1136
00:57:42,626 --> 00:57:43,992
I'm waitin', Nance!

1137
00:57:43,994 --> 00:57:46,028
Five hundred meters and closing fast!

1138
00:57:46,030 --> 00:57:49,565
What the--?!

1139
00:57:49,567 --> 00:57:51,667
[ WHIMPERING ]

1140
00:57:56,040 --> 00:57:58,640
WOMAN:<i> Reload.</i>

1141
00:57:58,642 --> 00:58:01,009
[ GRUNTS ]

1142
00:58:08,185 --> 00:58:10,819
What's next?

1143
00:58:12,923 --> 00:58:15,557
Straight shot... up the hill.

1144
00:58:15,559 --> 00:58:18,026
Okay.

1145
00:58:18,028 --> 00:58:22,097
Hey, Sarge, the new guy, what's his name again?

1146
00:58:25,169 --> 00:58:29,071
CAGE: We'll need a vehicle
to get further inland.

1147
00:58:29,073 --> 00:58:30,806
RITA: And what's the problem?

1148
00:58:30,808 --> 00:58:32,508
The problem is the ambush waiting for us down there.

1149
00:58:32,510 --> 00:58:34,076
They kill us before we find a working car.

1150
00:58:34,078 --> 00:58:35,978
Okay. So, what's
the current plan?

1151
00:58:35,980 --> 00:58:37,980
The two cars we haven't tried yet.

1152
00:58:37,982 --> 00:58:39,147
The minivan... yep.

1153
00:58:39,149 --> 00:58:41,083
...and the green S.U.V. Okay.

1154
00:58:41,085 --> 00:58:43,652
So I'll head for the S.U.V.,
draw the mimics to me.

1155
00:58:43,654 --> 00:58:44,953
You go for the minivan.

1156
00:58:44,955 --> 00:58:46,855
You get it started, just go, take off.

1157
00:58:46,857 --> 00:58:48,223
Do not wait for me. Okay.

1158
00:58:48,225 --> 00:58:50,092
Whoa-- just...

1159
00:58:50,094 --> 00:58:53,929
Don't forget to disconnect the
caravan before you take off.

1160
00:58:53,931 --> 00:58:55,163
You are going to be in a hurry

1161
00:58:55,165 --> 00:58:56,732
and you don't want any dead weight.

1162
00:59:05,109 --> 00:59:07,709
[ CRASHING ]

1163
00:59:20,090 --> 00:59:21,223
[ ENGINE SPUTTERING ]

1164
00:59:21,225 --> 00:59:22,691
Come on.

1165
00:59:22,693 --> 00:59:25,727
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

1166
00:59:34,038 --> 00:59:36,939
[ HORN HONKING ]

1167
00:59:36,941 --> 00:59:38,707
Come on, Cage!

1168
00:59:38,709 --> 00:59:40,709
WOMAN: <i>
...on the front line.</i>

1169
00:59:40,711 --> 00:59:42,678
<i>Our troops have suffered heavy casualties.</i>

1170
00:59:42,680 --> 00:59:44,913
<i>The enemy has breached security at Dover.</i>

1171
00:59:44,915 --> 00:59:46,348
<i>And all are advised to...
</i> I can't see.

1172
00:59:46,350 --> 00:59:48,116
<i>...seek shelter as
a matter of urgency.</i>

1173
00:59:48,118 --> 00:59:50,118
Can you? <i>In further updates,</i>

1174
00:59:50,120 --> 00:59:52,721
<i>mimics have now been sighted at Portsmouth, Brighton</i>

1175
00:59:52,723 --> 00:59:55,724
<i>and as far inland as Horsham.</i>

1176
00:59:55,726 --> 00:59:57,993
<i>The government advice at this point</i>

1177
00:59:57,995 --> 01:00:00,696
<i>is to stay where you are and remain calm.</i>

1178
01:00:00,698 --> 01:00:02,130
<i>If you are in a vehicle,</i>

1179
01:00:02,132 --> 01:00:05,601
<i>please lock doors and stay inside.</i>

1180
01:00:05,603 --> 01:00:07,869
<i>We are-- are now hearing accounts</i>

1181
01:00:07,871 --> 01:00:11,039
<i>of mimic attacks at Canterbury, Farnham,</i>

1182
01:00:11,041 --> 01:00:13,642
<i>and-- we-- we-- I'm sorry.</i>

1183
01:00:13,644 --> 01:00:15,611
<i>The enemy has reached London.</i>

1184
01:00:15,613 --> 01:00:16,612
<i>Repeat...</i>

1185
01:00:16,614 --> 01:00:19,081
<i>London is under attack.</i>

1186
01:00:21,652 --> 01:00:24,720
It's good driving.

1187
01:00:24,722 --> 01:00:26,154
I forgot to unhook the trailer.

1188
01:00:39,937 --> 01:00:42,170
<i>Engaged.</i>

1189
01:00:57,821 --> 01:00:59,821
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

1190
01:01:11,835 --> 01:01:14,403
You don't talk much.

1191
01:01:14,405 --> 01:01:16,405
I'm not a fan.

1192
01:01:16,407 --> 01:01:17,973
Of talking?

1193
01:01:17,975 --> 01:01:21,043
Not a fan of talking. No.

1194
01:01:21,045 --> 01:01:25,180
You know you eventually do talk to me.

1195
01:01:25,182 --> 01:01:27,182
It's usually around Lyons.

1196
01:01:27,184 --> 01:01:30,085
You tell me about the time you
went there with your family.

1197
01:01:30,087 --> 01:01:33,288
Your brother got lost.

1198
01:01:33,290 --> 01:01:35,791
I've never been to Lyons.

1199
01:01:35,793 --> 01:01:38,827
You tell me your middle name.

1200
01:01:38,829 --> 01:01:42,097
Peyton.

1201
01:01:42,099 --> 01:01:44,900
That's not my middle name.

1202
01:01:48,872 --> 01:01:52,708
You found your brother in the arcade, by the way.

1203
01:01:52,710 --> 01:01:56,044
Well, maybe I made it all up just to keep you quiet.

1204
01:01:56,046 --> 01:01:57,446
But you do talk to me.

1205
01:01:57,448 --> 01:02:00,182
Cage, I do not need to get to know you.

1206
01:02:00,184 --> 01:02:01,950
And if you knew what was good for you,

1207
01:02:01,952 --> 01:02:03,885
you wouldn't want to get to know me either.

1208
01:02:03,887 --> 01:02:05,987
It's the only way you make it through this thing.

1209
01:02:05,989 --> 01:02:09,024
What about Hendricks?
You get to know him?

1210
01:02:09,026 --> 01:02:10,892
How do you know that name?

1211
01:02:10,894 --> 01:02:12,194
You mentioned him.

1212
01:02:12,196 --> 01:02:13,795
That's not possible.

1213
01:02:13,797 --> 01:02:15,731
Then how do I know his name?

1214
01:02:15,733 --> 01:02:18,500
When did I mention him?
Under what circumstance?

1215
01:02:18,502 --> 01:02:21,203
Is he why you won't talk to me?

1216
01:02:24,208 --> 01:02:27,843
Don't ever mention his name again.

1217
01:02:27,845 --> 01:02:31,079
Why? Are you... in love with him?
He's dead.

1218
01:02:34,051 --> 01:02:37,119
And I watched him die three hundred times,

1219
01:02:37,121 --> 01:02:39,454
and I remember... every detail.

1220
01:02:39,456 --> 01:02:41,156
I remember everything.

1221
01:02:41,158 --> 01:02:43,892
So I don't need to talk about it.

1222
01:02:47,397 --> 01:02:49,097
I'm sorry.

1223
01:02:49,099 --> 01:02:51,266
It's just war.

1224
01:02:54,238 --> 01:02:57,939
[ BEEPING ]

1225
01:03:18,862 --> 01:03:23,899
[ ELECTRICITY POWERS DOWN ]

1226
01:03:51,962 --> 01:03:54,196
[ LIGHT CLATTER ]

1227
01:03:54,198 --> 01:03:56,298
There's nothing here.
Let's keep going.

1228
01:04:19,356 --> 01:04:21,289
We have to find the keys.

1229
01:04:21,291 --> 01:04:23,358
Let's just siphon the gas.

1230
01:04:23,360 --> 01:04:25,894
Oh, why drive when we can fly?

1231
01:04:25,896 --> 01:04:27,329
In<i> that</i> thing?

1232
01:04:27,331 --> 01:04:30,932
[ SIGHS ] Let me guess.
You're afraid of heights.

1233
01:04:30,934 --> 01:04:32,033
I'm afraid of crashing.

1234
01:04:32,035 --> 01:04:33,602
And not at all ashamed to admit it.

1235
01:04:33,604 --> 01:04:35,937
You'll be fine, Cage. You'll learn.
[ GRUNTS ]

1236
01:04:35,939 --> 01:04:38,240
What is it?

1237
01:04:38,242 --> 01:04:40,175
It's nothing. I'm fine.

1238
01:04:40,177 --> 01:04:42,277
What is it? It's nothing.

1239
01:04:42,279 --> 01:04:43,411
Rita.

1240
01:04:46,250 --> 01:04:48,984
Let me see.

1241
01:04:55,259 --> 01:04:58,293
[ GROANS ]

1242
01:05:08,171 --> 01:05:10,572
We have to find the keys to the helicopter.

1243
01:05:10,574 --> 01:05:13,308
I'm sure they're around here somewhere.

1244
01:05:13,310 --> 01:05:15,543
You know the Heli's full of fuel, though.

1245
01:05:15,545 --> 01:05:18,113
I found a hose.

1246
01:05:18,115 --> 01:05:20,015
We're flying, Cage.

1247
01:05:22,953 --> 01:05:25,620
Let's just say we find the keys.

1248
01:05:25,622 --> 01:05:28,256
You know? Get that
helicopter started.

1249
01:05:28,258 --> 01:05:30,992
We don't have our jackets or ammunition.

1250
01:05:30,994 --> 01:05:33,395
It's gonna be dark in a few hours.

1251
01:05:33,397 --> 01:05:39,367
Might be better off just going back to the farmhouse.

1252
01:05:39,369 --> 01:05:41,069
Seeing what we could salvage.

1253
01:05:41,071 --> 01:05:42,671
You know? Spend
the night there.

1254
01:05:42,673 --> 01:05:44,406
Come back here in the morning.

1255
01:05:44,408 --> 01:05:48,410
And curl up by the fire and open a bottle of wine.

1256
01:05:48,412 --> 01:05:50,412
[ CHUCKLES ]

1257
01:05:50,414 --> 01:05:51,579
[ GUN COCKS ]

1258
01:05:51,581 --> 01:05:53,014
I think we should just reset.

1259
01:05:53,016 --> 01:05:54,482
Whoa! It's a dead end.

1260
01:05:54,484 --> 01:05:56,017
Hey, just--

1261
01:05:56,019 --> 01:05:57,585
if it's all the same to you, I'm tired.

1262
01:05:57,587 --> 01:05:59,421
I'm in pain. I'd rather
just start fresh.

1263
01:05:59,423 --> 01:06:01,056
I'll tell you what.
Take a few minutes.

1264
01:06:01,058 --> 01:06:03,325
Coffee's ready. I'll
look around for the keys.

1265
01:06:03,327 --> 01:06:04,326
That's productive.

1266
01:06:04,328 --> 01:06:06,027
Ten minutes. Okay.

1267
01:06:06,029 --> 01:06:07,362
And then I'm killing you.

1268
01:06:07,364 --> 01:06:09,431
Fine.

1269
01:06:09,433 --> 01:06:12,167
[ SIGHS ]

1270
01:06:12,169 --> 01:06:15,070
I can't believe you found coffee.

1271
01:06:16,373 --> 01:06:18,440
Thank you.

1272
01:06:18,442 --> 01:06:20,675
Oh.

1273
01:06:20,677 --> 01:06:22,377
Sugar, right?

1274
01:06:22,379 --> 01:06:24,479
Yeah.

1275
01:06:28,452 --> 01:06:29,484
[ CHUCKLES ]

1276
01:06:29,486 --> 01:06:30,719
Thank you.

1277
01:06:30,721 --> 01:06:32,520
Ah, hold on. Three.
You like three.

1278
01:06:46,436 --> 01:06:49,104
There's a shirt over there.
It should be your size.

1279
01:06:51,408 --> 01:06:53,008
[ DRAWERS OPENING, CLOSING ]

1280
01:06:56,546 --> 01:07:00,015
RITA: How many times
have we been here?

1281
01:07:04,788 --> 01:07:06,788
How many times?

1282
01:07:06,790 --> 01:07:10,425
Where are the keys?

1283
01:07:10,427 --> 01:07:12,027
Where are the goddamn keys?
Yeah, okay.

1284
01:07:12,029 --> 01:07:14,529
[ KEYS JINGLE ]

1285
01:07:14,531 --> 01:07:17,132
[ GRUNTS ] You can fly it, can't you?

1286
01:07:17,134 --> 01:07:19,801
No. Well, yes. I
mean, I can take off.

1287
01:07:19,803 --> 01:07:21,803
I'm still working on my landing, so...

1288
01:07:21,805 --> 01:07:23,438
What are we still doing here?

1289
01:07:23,440 --> 01:07:24,672
You're wasting time!

1290
01:07:24,674 --> 01:07:26,107
Rita, if you start that engine you die.

1291
01:07:29,146 --> 01:07:31,346
This is far as you go.

1292
01:07:31,348 --> 01:07:33,581
No matter what I do...

1293
01:07:33,583 --> 01:07:37,085
This is as far as you ever make it.

1294
01:07:43,760 --> 01:07:47,128
There's a mimic buried twenty yards away.

1295
01:07:47,130 --> 01:07:50,098
It attacks when you start the engine.

1296
01:07:50,100 --> 01:07:53,568
Get your weapon and get in the helicopter, Cage.

1297
01:07:53,570 --> 01:07:56,704
There's more in the field back there.

1298
01:07:58,141 --> 01:07:59,574
Only one of us ever makes it.

1299
01:07:59,576 --> 01:08:01,209
Get in.

1300
01:08:01,211 --> 01:08:02,711
The only thing we haven't tried is the version

1301
01:08:02,712 --> 01:08:03,845
where you walk away. Just
go back to the farmhouse.

1302
01:08:03,847 --> 01:08:05,213
There's a cellar. There's food.

1303
01:08:05,215 --> 01:08:07,082
You wait there till I get back.

1304
01:08:07,084 --> 01:08:08,216
You'll be safe.

1305
01:08:08,218 --> 01:08:10,285
I'm a soldier. I volunteered.

1306
01:08:10,287 --> 01:08:11,619
I'm not walking away.

1307
01:08:11,621 --> 01:08:13,088
You die here.

1308
01:08:13,090 --> 01:08:14,222
Right here.

1309
01:08:14,224 --> 01:08:18,159
[ SIGHS ] I... can't save you.

1310
01:08:18,161 --> 01:08:21,362
And if I go on and kill the Omega, you're dead.

1311
01:08:21,364 --> 01:08:23,098
Forever.

1312
01:08:23,100 --> 01:08:26,468
Why does it matter what happens to me?

1313
01:08:26,470 --> 01:08:30,405
I wish...

1314
01:08:30,407 --> 01:08:33,775
I didn't know you...

1315
01:08:33,777 --> 01:08:37,278
But I do.

1316
01:09:11,748 --> 01:09:14,816
[ GRUNTING ]

1317
01:09:32,435 --> 01:09:34,903
[ GRUNTING ]

1318
01:09:37,707 --> 01:09:40,341
[ PANTING ]

1319
01:10:06,403 --> 01:10:09,370
My middle name...

1320
01:10:09,372 --> 01:10:11,472
Is rose.

1321
01:10:14,711 --> 01:10:16,578
[ GASPS LIGHTLY ]

1322
01:10:16,580 --> 01:10:17,946
[ MIMIC APPROACHING ]

1323
01:10:30,760 --> 01:10:33,294
SERGEANT: On your feet, maggot!

1324
01:10:33,296 --> 01:10:37,265
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

1325
01:10:37,267 --> 01:10:39,434
[ WOMEN SPEAKING NATIVE
LANGUAGE OVER P.A. ]

1326
01:10:43,907 --> 01:10:46,341
FARELL: The good news is
there's hope for you, Private.

1327
01:10:46,343 --> 01:10:48,843
Hope in the form of glorious combat.

1328
01:10:48,845 --> 01:10:50,812
Battle is the great redeemer,

1329
01:10:50,814 --> 01:10:54,849
the fiery crucible in which the
only true heroes are forged.

1330
01:10:54,851 --> 01:10:57,285
[ VOICE FADING ] The one place where all men...

1331
01:11:05,695 --> 01:11:07,662
Yes?

1332
01:11:07,664 --> 01:11:10,965
Who said you could talk to me?

1333
01:11:14,037 --> 01:11:17,372
Have I got something on my face, soldier?

1334
01:11:17,374 --> 01:11:21,943
I'm sorry to disturb you, Sergeant.

1335
01:11:43,800 --> 01:11:45,500
All right, man, let's get this show on the road.

1336
01:11:45,502 --> 01:11:46,401
I gotta suit up.

1337
01:11:46,403 --> 01:11:47,735
[ EQUIPMENT POWERING UP ]

1338
01:11:47,737 --> 01:11:49,037
SKINNER: Come on,
Kimmel, let's have it!

1339
01:11:49,039 --> 01:11:50,071
Where's your helmet?

1340
01:11:50,073 --> 01:11:53,074
Never wear one.

1341
01:11:53,076 --> 01:11:55,410
It's a distraction.

1342
01:11:55,412 --> 01:11:58,813
Have you been drinking?

1343
01:11:58,815 --> 01:12:01,082
I need three more clips
of five-five-six,

1344
01:12:01,084 --> 01:12:04,452
eight grenades and an extra battery.

1345
01:12:07,724 --> 01:12:08,856
Get it.

1346
01:12:15,532 --> 01:12:17,065
SKINNER: 'Ey!

1347
01:12:17,067 --> 01:12:18,833
Oi, mate!

1348
01:12:18,835 --> 01:12:20,735
I think there's something wrong with your suit.

1349
01:12:20,737 --> 01:12:24,105
There's a dead guy in it.

1350
01:12:24,107 --> 01:12:27,408
Woo-hoo! We made it!

1351
01:12:27,410 --> 01:12:28,910
Thank god, we made it!

1352
01:12:28,912 --> 01:12:30,645
Whoo--!

1353
01:12:38,521 --> 01:12:39,954
[ AUTOMATIC GUNFIRE ]

1354
01:13:10,787 --> 01:13:13,154
[ WIND RUSHING ]

1355
01:13:26,903 --> 01:13:29,704
[ HISSING ]

1356
01:14:12,982 --> 01:14:14,615
[ GRUNTING ]

1357
01:14:18,621 --> 01:14:21,155
[ CREATURE SCREECHING ]

1358
01:14:30,600 --> 01:14:34,836
Finish it!

1359
01:14:34,838 --> 01:14:36,571
[ SCREECHING CONTINUES ]

1360
01:14:53,056 --> 01:14:56,023
[ SCREECHING CONTINUES ]

1361
01:15:27,056 --> 01:15:29,991
It isn't there.

1362
01:15:29,993 --> 01:15:31,926
What do you mean the Omega isn't there?

1363
01:15:31,928 --> 01:15:33,794
My guess is it never was.
They knew we were coming.

1364
01:15:33,796 --> 01:15:34,662
They ambushed us.

1365
01:15:34,664 --> 01:15:36,063
The visions were a trap.

1366
01:15:36,065 --> 01:15:40,067
Just like Rita's visions were a trap at Verdun.

1367
01:15:40,069 --> 01:15:43,070
It could have killed me but it didn't.

1368
01:15:43,072 --> 01:15:44,105
It's after my blood.

1369
01:15:44,107 --> 01:15:46,140
So they know who you are.

1370
01:15:46,142 --> 01:15:49,110
They-- they want their power back.

1371
01:15:49,112 --> 01:15:51,112
And they're gonna get it one way or another.

1372
01:15:51,114 --> 01:15:52,713
Unless we find the Omega.

1373
01:15:52,715 --> 01:15:54,982
The-- there isn't any other way.
We're finished.

1374
01:15:54,984 --> 01:15:57,118
No. We're<i> not</i> finished.

1375
01:15:57,120 --> 01:15:58,586
That doesn't work. I-I
can't get it to work.

1376
01:15:58,588 --> 01:16:00,121
You built a prototype
at Whitehall--

1377
01:16:00,123 --> 01:16:02,256
yes, and I got fired for it, thank you very much.

1378
01:16:02,258 --> 01:16:03,658
Wh-what is this thing, anyway?

1379
01:16:03,660 --> 01:16:04,725
It's a transponder.

1380
01:16:04,727 --> 01:16:06,260
You stick it into the Alpha,

1381
01:16:06,262 --> 01:16:09,196
and it taps into the wavelength
connecting it to the Omega.

1382
01:16:09,198 --> 01:16:10,598
That's the idea, anyway.

1383
01:16:10,600 --> 01:16:12,066
But I can't get it to work.

1384
01:16:12,068 --> 01:16:14,101
Not with the equipment I have on hand.

1385
01:16:14,103 --> 01:16:17,004
How do we get you what you need?

1386
01:16:17,006 --> 01:16:18,339
Well, that's the thing.

1387
01:16:18,341 --> 01:16:20,174
I mean, when I was at whitehall I built one.

1388
01:16:20,176 --> 01:16:21,609
I was even ready to test it.

1389
01:16:21,611 --> 01:16:23,144
When I told my superiors about it...

1390
01:16:23,146 --> 01:16:24,078
Well, I lost my job.

1391
01:16:24,080 --> 01:16:25,680
They thought he was crazy.

1392
01:16:25,682 --> 01:16:27,748
So all we need to do is go to Whitehall.

1393
01:16:27,750 --> 01:16:30,685
You'd be arrested ten feet from the front door.

1394
01:16:30,687 --> 01:16:32,153
Psych ward. Dissection.
Remember?

1395
01:16:32,155 --> 01:16:35,623
Hey, hey, hey! Aren't you
forgetting something?

1396
01:16:35,625 --> 01:16:37,959
The transponder requires a live Alpha to make it work.

1397
01:16:37,961 --> 01:16:42,196
We don't need one. We
got the next best thing.

1398
01:16:44,200 --> 01:16:46,701
When the Chinese delegation comes out...

1399
01:16:46,703 --> 01:16:48,769
We pick up the pace.

1400
01:16:48,771 --> 01:16:52,640
This guy with the yellow armband always recognizes you...

1401
01:16:52,642 --> 01:16:56,177
So just keep your head down and stay to my right.

1402
01:17:02,018 --> 01:17:05,152
Nicely done.

1403
01:17:06,155 --> 01:17:08,255
Three, two, one.

1404
01:17:08,257 --> 01:17:09,290
Go.

1405
01:17:09,292 --> 01:17:10,224
One...

1406
01:17:12,729 --> 01:17:14,395
Six, seven...

1407
01:17:14,397 --> 01:17:16,097
Eight...

1408
01:17:21,204 --> 01:17:22,670
[ DEVICE BEEPS ]

1409
01:17:22,672 --> 01:17:24,672
And, turn. [ SNAPS FINGERS ]

1410
01:17:24,674 --> 01:17:27,775
Okay. Keep walking. Just
stare straight ahead.

1411
01:17:28,911 --> 01:17:30,645
MAN: Robinson.

1412
01:17:30,647 --> 01:17:32,346
I've asked not to be disturbed.

1413
01:17:32,348 --> 01:17:34,115
This had better be critical.

1414
01:17:34,117 --> 01:17:35,416
CAGE: The fate of mankind.

1415
01:17:35,418 --> 01:17:36,817
Critical enough?

1416
01:17:36,819 --> 01:17:38,819
I don't believe what I'm seeing.

1417
01:17:38,821 --> 01:17:41,222
I've had more than my share of that.

1418
01:17:41,224 --> 01:17:44,191
RITA: Sit down, General.
Stay away from the desk.

1419
01:17:44,193 --> 01:17:46,827
I'd take her very seriously if I were you.

1420
01:17:46,829 --> 01:17:49,997
Have to hand it to you, Major.

1421
01:17:49,999 --> 01:17:51,932
When you left this office today,

1422
01:17:51,934 --> 01:17:53,834
I never imagined you'd be back,

1423
01:17:53,836 --> 01:17:56,103
let alone with my most decorated soldier.

1424
01:17:56,105 --> 01:17:57,672
I'm gonna tell ya a story, General.

1425
01:17:57,674 --> 01:17:59,373
And, at first, it's gonna sound ridiculous,

1426
01:17:59,375 --> 01:18:01,242
but the longer I talk, the more
rational it's going to appear.

1427
01:18:01,244 --> 01:18:02,810
[ PHONE RINGS ] Tell him you'll call back.

1428
01:18:02,812 --> 01:18:04,445
Tell who?

1429
01:18:04,447 --> 01:18:06,247
Major General Beaumont, calling from Halifax.

1430
01:18:06,249 --> 01:18:08,049
His plane has just been delayed.
Bad weather.

1431
01:18:08,051 --> 01:18:09,817
Yes.

1432
01:18:12,255 --> 01:18:15,222
Thank you, Beaumont.
I'll call you back.

1433
01:18:17,093 --> 01:18:18,993
Tomorrow's invasion is a slaughter.

1434
01:18:18,995 --> 01:18:21,729
I'm dead within five minutes of landing on that beach,

1435
01:18:21,731 --> 01:18:24,065
along with every other soldier you are sending.

1436
01:18:24,067 --> 01:18:26,400
And that's because the enemy knows we're coming.

1437
01:18:26,402 --> 01:18:28,269
How do I know this?
Before I died,

1438
01:18:28,271 --> 01:18:30,738
I killed a mimic, only this one was different.

1439
01:18:30,740 --> 01:18:32,940
It passed something on to me.
In my blood.

1440
01:18:32,942 --> 01:18:35,209
Now I live the same day over and over again.

1441
01:18:35,211 --> 01:18:36,243
Just like they do.

1442
01:18:36,245 --> 01:18:37,878
Just like Sergeant Vrataski...

1443
01:18:37,880 --> 01:18:39,280
At Verdun.

1444
01:18:39,282 --> 01:18:41,882
Tell your secretary everything's fine.

1445
01:18:41,884 --> 01:18:43,217
Beg your pardon?

1446
01:18:45,888 --> 01:18:48,155
Um, I'm... sorry, General.
I thought you were alone.

1447
01:18:48,157 --> 01:18:49,890
It's fine.

1448
01:18:49,892 --> 01:18:51,926
She typed up those orders for you to authorize.

1449
01:18:51,928 --> 01:18:54,095
But she left out the ones referring to the fuel dump

1450
01:18:54,097 --> 01:18:56,831
at Greenwich.

1451
01:18:56,833 --> 01:18:58,299
Your name is Iris.

1452
01:18:58,301 --> 01:19:00,935
Your birthday is September seventeenth.

1453
01:19:00,937 --> 01:19:02,503
The General quietly pulled some strings,

1454
01:19:02,505 --> 01:19:04,004
stationed your only son in Australia,

1455
01:19:04,006 --> 01:19:05,506
as far from the war as possible.

1456
01:19:05,508 --> 01:19:08,042
Tell the General his dinner's just been canceled.

1457
01:19:08,044 --> 01:19:09,276
The call came in just now.

1458
01:19:09,278 --> 01:19:12,847
Your dinner was canceled.

1459
01:19:12,849 --> 01:19:15,349
You forgot the fuel dump.

1460
01:19:15,351 --> 01:19:18,152
Thank you, Iris.
That'll be all.

1461
01:19:25,962 --> 01:19:27,128
Cage, let's go.

1462
01:19:27,130 --> 01:19:28,295
Rita.

1463
01:19:28,297 --> 01:19:30,965
Let me just-- what are we doing?

1464
01:19:30,967 --> 01:19:32,366
Please, don't shoot him again.
Okay?

1465
01:19:32,368 --> 01:19:35,136
Just-- just--

1466
01:19:35,138 --> 01:19:36,771
[ SIGHS ]

1467
01:19:36,773 --> 01:19:38,439
General, thi--

1468
01:19:38,441 --> 01:19:41,442
this isn't the first time we've
had this conversation, okay?

1469
01:19:41,444 --> 01:19:43,978
That's-that's-because
you're-you're stubborn.

1470
01:19:43,980 --> 01:19:46,380
You won't believe me when I tell ya

1471
01:19:46,382 --> 01:19:48,048
that Dr. Carter was right.

1472
01:19:48,050 --> 01:19:50,284
That the enemy can manipulate time.

1473
01:19:50,286 --> 01:19:51,852
The invasion will fail.

1474
01:19:51,854 --> 01:19:54,355
No matter how many bodies you throw at it.

1475
01:19:54,357 --> 01:19:56,423
The only way to win this war

1476
01:19:56,425 --> 01:19:59,860
is by finding this power source of the mimic horde

1477
01:19:59,862 --> 01:20:00,995
and killing it.

1478
01:20:00,997 --> 01:20:02,797
And the only means of finding it

1479
01:20:02,799 --> 01:20:04,365
is in that safe right there.

1480
01:20:07,003 --> 01:20:08,936
No matter how many times we have this conversation...

1481
01:20:08,938 --> 01:20:10,404
You refuse to accept

1482
01:20:10,406 --> 01:20:12,506
that the enemy breaks through to London tomorrow

1483
01:20:12,508 --> 01:20:14,074
and we lose.

1484
01:20:14,076 --> 01:20:16,877
We lose everything.

1485
01:20:22,051 --> 01:20:24,251
Let's say for one moment...

1486
01:20:24,253 --> 01:20:27,221
That I can't rationally explain...

1487
01:20:27,223 --> 01:20:30,357
Your impressive parlor tricks.

1488
01:20:30,359 --> 01:20:32,426
[ KEYPAD BEEPING, SAFE DOOR OPENS ]

1489
01:20:32,428 --> 01:20:35,196
Dr. Carter told me...

1490
01:20:35,198 --> 01:20:37,898
This device requires a live mimic to work.

1491
01:20:37,900 --> 01:20:39,233
What use is it to you?

1492
01:20:39,235 --> 01:20:41,836
That's my concern.

1493
01:20:41,838 --> 01:20:43,237
On the contrary.

1494
01:20:43,239 --> 01:20:45,039
According to you, this concerns the whole world.

1495
01:20:45,041 --> 01:20:46,340
Well, what would you do

1496
01:20:46,342 --> 01:20:48,943
if you believed everything I just told you?

1497
01:20:48,945 --> 01:20:51,378
I would locate this...

1498
01:20:51,380 --> 01:20:53,614
Omega... and bomb it out of existence.

1499
01:20:53,616 --> 01:20:56,016
You're not mentally equipped to fight this thing.

1500
01:20:56,018 --> 01:20:57,852
And you never will be.

1501
01:21:13,436 --> 01:21:16,237
What do we do now?

1502
01:21:16,239 --> 01:21:19,406
I don't know. We've
never gotten this far.

1503
01:21:24,547 --> 01:21:26,080
That was easy.

1504
01:21:26,082 --> 01:21:27,348
Now! Stop!

1505
01:21:27,350 --> 01:21:29,383
Stop right there! Don't move!

1506
01:21:29,385 --> 01:21:31,085
Nobody move!

1507
01:21:31,087 --> 01:21:33,087
Weapon!

1508
01:21:33,089 --> 01:21:34,955
[ GUNSHOT, TIRES SCREECH ]

1509
01:21:34,957 --> 01:21:36,123
MAN: Stop!

1510
01:21:40,096 --> 01:21:41,996
They're off and away!
[ YELLS INDISTINCTLY ]

1511
01:21:41,998 --> 01:21:43,097
What am I supposed to do with this?

1512
01:21:43,099 --> 01:21:46,133
Stick it in your leg. Do it!

1513
01:21:51,107 --> 01:21:52,106
[ GRUNTS ]

1514
01:21:52,108 --> 01:21:54,074
[ GASPING ]

1515
01:21:56,946 --> 01:21:59,013
[ TIRES SCREECHING ]

1516
01:22:03,352 --> 01:22:05,920
[ ECHOING ] Cage, what's happening?

1517
01:22:05,922 --> 01:22:07,922
Talk to me.

1518
01:22:07,924 --> 01:22:10,658
I feel it. It's tak-it's
taking me there.

1519
01:22:10,660 --> 01:22:13,928
What do you see?

1520
01:22:13,930 --> 01:22:15,663
It's-it's the louvre.

1521
01:22:15,665 --> 01:22:17,231
Where? Where are you?

1522
01:22:17,233 --> 01:22:20,401
I'm inside now. It's flooded.

1523
01:22:20,403 --> 01:22:22,569
Now I'm going down. I'm
in a-I'm in a garage.

1524
01:22:22,571 --> 01:22:24,204
A garage underneath the museum.

1525
01:22:24,206 --> 01:22:26,640
The Omega. Can you see it?

1526
01:22:29,145 --> 01:22:30,611
[ GASPS ]

1527
01:22:32,315 --> 01:22:33,981
It's in Paris.

1528
01:22:50,099 --> 01:22:51,565
[ GRUNTING ]

1529
01:22:51,567 --> 01:22:53,600
Rita!

1530
01:22:56,172 --> 01:22:58,072
[ GRUNTS ]

1531
01:22:58,074 --> 01:23:00,174
[ VEHICLE BEEPING, SIREN WAILING ]

1532
01:23:00,176 --> 01:23:02,042
MAN: Turn your head!

1533
01:23:02,044 --> 01:23:04,578
Stay in the car!

1534
01:23:04,580 --> 01:23:07,581
Move away from the car!
Move away!

1535
01:23:09,485 --> 01:23:12,019
[ MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY ]

1536
01:23:30,539 --> 01:23:33,440
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

1537
01:23:33,442 --> 01:23:36,043
What have you done?

1538
01:23:36,045 --> 01:23:38,178
What have you done?

1539
01:23:38,180 --> 01:23:39,480
[ BEEPING STOPS ]

1540
01:23:39,482 --> 01:23:44,118
You'll be fine. You
just needed blood.

1541
01:23:44,120 --> 01:23:46,053
You don't know what you've just done.

1542
01:23:46,055 --> 01:23:47,021
I'm not allowed to talk to you.

1543
01:23:47,023 --> 01:23:49,089
I was with someone.

1544
01:23:49,091 --> 01:23:52,226
Rita Vrataski. Is she alive?

1545
01:23:52,228 --> 01:23:54,061
Rita Vrataski.

1546
01:23:54,063 --> 01:23:56,030
Please.

1547
01:23:56,032 --> 01:23:58,065
Just tell me that.

1548
01:23:59,702 --> 01:24:01,769
Please tell me.

1549
01:24:01,771 --> 01:24:03,637
I'm sorry.

1550
01:24:19,455 --> 01:24:21,321
[ GRUNTING ]

1551
01:24:28,431 --> 01:24:30,497
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING IN DISTANCE ]

1552
01:24:30,499 --> 01:24:33,467
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES, MAN COUGHING ]

1553
01:24:33,469 --> 01:24:37,504
[ ALARM BLARING IN DISTANCE ]

1554
01:24:40,543 --> 01:24:43,143
I was out of those things in three minutes flat, Cage.

1555
01:24:43,145 --> 01:24:44,211
What's wrong with you?

1556
01:24:44,213 --> 01:24:45,312
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

1557
01:24:45,314 --> 01:24:47,448
I thought you were dead.

1558
01:24:47,450 --> 01:24:49,283
Not yet.

1559
01:24:54,290 --> 01:24:56,190
Sorry, Cage. No! Whoa-whoa.

1560
01:24:56,192 --> 01:24:57,858
Wait! Wait! I'm out. I'm out.

1561
01:24:57,860 --> 01:25:00,694
They gave me blood.

1562
01:25:00,696 --> 01:25:02,696
[ ALARM CONTINUES ]

1563
01:25:02,698 --> 01:25:05,699
I lost the power.

1564
01:25:05,701 --> 01:25:08,469
I feel it.

1565
01:25:08,471 --> 01:25:12,239
I can't reset the day anymore.

1566
01:25:14,310 --> 01:25:18,145
[ SIRENS WAILING, INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

1567
01:25:18,147 --> 01:25:19,746
WOMAN:<i> Be advised:</i>

1568
01:25:19,748 --> 01:25:21,548
<i>Hanger f-nine is out of</i>
<i>bounds until further notice.</i>

1569
01:25:21,550 --> 01:25:22,649
[ DOG BARKING ]

1570
01:25:22,651 --> 01:25:25,319
